    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9393" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φεύγω</span></b> , inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φευγέμεν</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αι</span>),
          ipf. iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φεύγεσκεν</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φεύξομαι</span>, aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔφυγον, φύγον</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φύγῃ</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σι</span>), inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φυγέειν</span>, perf. opt. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεφεύγοι</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεφυγότες,
            πεφυζότες</span>, mid. perf. part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεφυγμένος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">flee, flee from, escape;</span> esp.
          flee one's country, go into exile, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἵ̄κετο
            φεύγων</span>, came as fugitive, <i><span class="en">Od.
            16.424</span></i>; often trans., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θάλασσαν,
            θάνατον</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.362</span></i>;
          fig., with a thing as subj., <i><span class="en">Il.
          8.137</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 4.350</span></i>; mid., 
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεφυγμένος</span>, usually w. acc.; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀέθλων</span>, ‘escaped’ from toils, <i><span class="en">Od. 1.18</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
